<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Remarks</emphasis>
. This new species can be readily distinguished from all other 
<emphasis box="[1006,1152,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Vertomannus</emphasis>
species by the head with a very short “neck” and a small body. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng" authorityName="Zheng" box="[732,1011,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Vertomannus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollum" subGenus="Vertomannus">
<emphasis box="[732,932,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">V.(V.) brevicollum</emphasis>
Zheng
</taxonomicName>
in having fore femora not incrassate, the fore tibiae straight, the anterior pronotal lobe not longer than the posterior lobe, the neck of the head not longer than the postocular distance; but the fore femora of the new species armed with two spines (there is only one in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,350,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Vertomannus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicollum" subGenus="Vertomannus">
<emphasis box="[151,350,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">V.(V.) brevicollum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the color pattern of antennae and pronotum, paramere and sperm reservoir are also different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
